        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-09-26T20:23:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think it is better not to couple these two concepts. One is whether invocation is still ongoing, and another whether it is destined to be incomplete (forever). I\u0027ve clarified that incomplete state is terminal. Does it help?\n\nreplying to Chan here too, since we both threads seem to be talking about the same thing. Looks like this term is ambiguous. Meanings: 1) it is done 2) it lacks some items. I meant the latter. Need help with English here, ideas for a better word?",
      "parentUuid": "5fa83224_26fda9d0",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 40,
        "startChar": 22,
        "endLine": 40,
        "endChar": 23
      },
      "revId": "d2ffb568c6e244c33062576533d904c6a5275d31",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
