    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "217c469f_15aca228",
        "filename": "results/proto/v1/invocation.proto",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 40,
      "author": {
        "id": 1134874
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-09-26T23:04:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "How about \"The contents of the finalized invocation are complete\", and then \"Invocations not yet finalized do not have this field set\" (if accurate)?\n\nAs for a better word, I\u0027m not sure. How does \"interrupted\" sound? It\u0027s not /exactly/ the same, but should capture the notion that if we know it was interrupted, then we did know its state (i.e. was finalized)?\n\nOne difficulty is that IIRC proto3 doesn\u0027t differentiate between unset and default values.",
      "parentUuid": "c905939c_bb61e8da",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 40,
        "startChar": 22,
        "endLine": 40,
        "endChar": 23
      },
      "revId": "d2ffb568c6e244c33062576533d904c6a5275d31",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
